---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Trim @Brussels Sprouts{8%ounce} and halve through base. Cut @White Potatoes{1} in half. Toss potatoes with a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} on a #baking sheet{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast in oven until tender, ~{20-25%minutes} total (we'll add more to the sheet after ~{10%minutes}).

Toss Brussels sprouts with a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{} in a #medium bowl{}. Once potatoes have roasted ~{10%minutes}, remove from oven and give them a toss. Add Brussels sprouts to baking sheet. Return sheet to oven and continue roasting until both are tender and crisped, ~{10-15%minutes} more.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Shallot{1}. Trim, then thinly slice @Button Mushrooms{4%ounce}. Finely chop @Parsley{1/4%ounce}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Pat @Pork Chops{12%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}. Season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add to pan and cook to desired doneness, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside.

Add mushrooms and shallot to same pan. Cook, tossing occasionally, until softened, ~{3-5%minutes}. Stir in @Veggie Stock Concentrate{1} and @water{1/4%cup}, scraping up any browned bits from bottom. Bring to a boil, then remove from heat. Stir in @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon} and parsley. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide pork, Brussels sprouts, and potatoes between plates. Drizzle sauce over pork, making sure to add mushrooms, and serve.

> Pork chops blanketed in a creamy mushroom sauce is a recipe that's an oldie and a goodie. The combo of savory mushrooms, rich dairy, and lean pork is enduring and familiar, yet it never fails to remind you of how good it is every time. On the side, oven-roasted potatoes and Brussels sprouts complete this comfortingly classic meal.